[background arg="res://backgrounds/BACKGROUND_gm_inside.png" fade="0.0"]
[wait time="1.5"]
(She gazes wide eyed at all the confections around her.)
(The shop is breathtaking.)
join marzi (Casual Love) left
marzi (Casual Love): (Am...am I dreaming?!)
marzi (Casual Love): (No, I must have died on the bus ride and gone to heaven!!)
leave marzi
(She marvels at the surprisingly massive interior of the shop.)
(It is filled to the brim with perfect quality confections.)
(Undulating blown sugar globes hang in the air with a curious and brightly colored mist swirling within.)
(They hang in the air as if by magic.)
(There are glowing, levitating, and sparkling truffles in a rainbow of colors.)
(Marzi leans in to have a closer look at the cotton candy.)
(It swirls and twinkles, like each sugar cloud held it's own galaxy inside.)
(There are impressive display showpieces of modeling chocolate trees with marzipan fruits hanging from the branches...)
(...Pulled sugar birds are in nestled in the branches.)
(They tilt their heads and fix their shiny button eyes on Marzi, tweeting and cooing at her.)
(Marzi pinches her wrist.)
join marzi (Casual Surprised) left
marzi (Casual Surprised): Ouch!
marzi (Casual Amazed): (I'm not dreaming and I'm not dead!)
marzi (Casual Love): (This is real.)
marzi (Casual Anticipation): (THIS IS REEEEAL!!!)
marzi (Casual Amazed): (I knew The Gilded Macaron was supposed to be legendary...)
marzi (Casual Amazed): (But I didn't think it was literally magical!)
leave marzi
(A woman clears her throat and you hear her footsteps echo on the marble.)
join beatrix (Macaron) rightmost
beatrix (Macaron): Welcome! Welcome to The Gilded Macaron, my dear!
beatrix (Happy): Do step right in, please!
beatrix (Idle Neutral): I am Madame Beatrix Von Sweets, owner and operator of this humble establishment.
beatrix (Idle Neutral): A pleasure to meet you.
join marzi (Casual Happy) left
- Um...Um...Hi...Um...
	set {beatrix_points} -= "3"
	beatrix (Idle Neutral): Well aren't you such an... interesting girl!
	beatrix (Idle Neutral): With a fashion sense to match!
	beatrix (Idle Neutral): You must have a very eclectic palette.
	beatrix (Idle Neutral): We have an extra fresh batch of turkish delights that I think you'll love.
	beatrix (Idle Neutral): Our in house confectioners have enchanted them so that you feel the chill of falling snowflakes when you take a bite.
	beatrix (Idle Neutral): Would you like to try a sample before you purchase?
- Hiya! Nice to meet you too!
	set {beatrix_points} += "1"
	beatrix (Idle Neutral): My, what a confident girl you are!
	beatrix (Idle Neutral): With a fashion sense to match!
	beatrix (Idle Neutral): You must have a very bold palette.
	beatrix (Idle Neutral): Might I recommend our salted soft caramels?
	beatrix (Idle Neutral): Our in house confectioners have have enchanted them so they don't stick to your teeth!
	beatrix (Idle Neutral): Would you like to try a sample before you purchase?
- A pleasure to meet you as well, Madame.
	set {beatrix_points} += "5"
	beatrix (Idle Neutral): Ah, such pleasant manners.
	beatrix (Idle Neutral): A rarity in today's youth.
	beatrix (Idle Neutral): Impeccable fashion sense as well I see.
	beatrix (Idle Neutral): You must have a very refined palette.
	beatrix (Macaron): I must of course then recommend our house made macarons.
	beatrix (Macaron): You won't find another comparable.
	beatrix (Macaron): I personally oversee all the enchantments on our macarons.
	beatrix (Macaron): We rotate the flavor profiles and effects out every day.
	beatrix (Macaron): Today's theme is weather, so the yellow macarons taste like sundew-nice for warming up in the evening before bed.
	beatrix (Macaron): The blue ones tastes like a summer shower and you don't need a drink to wash it down.
	beatrix (Macaron): Green is lightning, white is hail, you get the picture.
	beatrix (Macaron): Would you like to try a sample before you purchase, young miss?
marzi (Casual Apologetic): Oh wow, that is such a tempting offer Madame Sweets.
marzi (Casual Serious): But I'm actually not a customer.
marzi (Casual Serious): I'm Marzipan Glace. Marzi for short.
marzi (Casual Happy): I saw the job posting about an opening in the confectionery.
marzi (Casual Happy): I brought my portfolio and my confectionery school diploma!
leave --All--
(The temperature in the room suddenly seems to drop ten degrees.)
(Beatrix's radiant smile vanishes instantly and is replaced by a cold, calculating stare.)
(She pulls a golden cell phone out of her pocket, her posture stiffening into absolute rigidity.)
(When she speaks again, her voice is flat and clipped.)
join beatrix (Unimpressed) rightmost
beatrix (Unimpressed): A job applicant. I see.
join marzi (Casual Concerned) left
marzi (Casual Concerned): (I feel so small right now...what happened to make her switch like that?)
marzi (Casual Confident): (Come on Marzi, don't let this deter you from your big chance!)
marzi (Casual Confident): Yes Madame. I just graduated and-
leave --All--
(Beatrix holds up a single, immaculate finger to silence her.)
(She steps closer to Marzi, and takes the portfolio from her hands.)
(She inspects it like a hawk inspects a field mouse.)
join beatrix (Dour Lookdown) rightmost
beatrix (Dour Lookdown): Confectionery school. I see. So, no formal magic discipline?
beatrix (Dour Lookdown): Never been part of a coven...
beatrix (Dour Lookdown): (Beatrix gestures sharply towards the overstuffed portfolio, which has a few rogue formula sketches sticking out of the zipper.)
beatrix (Dour Lookdown): Your presentation is chaotic at best.
beatrix (Dour Lookdown): There is powdered sugar on your left shoe.
beatrix (Dour Lookdown): And I don't know If I would have chosen THAT outfit for introductions with a prospective employer...
beatrix (Dour Lookdown): But I do think my customers would enjoy your style...
beatrix (Idle Dour): Many of them come in after shopping at the boutique next door.
beatrix (Dour Lookdown): You also have ink-or perhaps food coloring-smudged on your wrist.
beatrix (Dour Lookdown): I run a tight ship around here, Ms. Glace.
beatrix (Dour Lookdown): Do you really think you can work to the high standards required to keep The Gilded Macaron's flawless reputation?
join marzi (Casual Concerned) left
marzi (Casual Concerned): (Marzi tries to hide her stained wrist behind her back.)
marzi (Casual Concerned): I...I know I look a little scattered, but I'm a fast learner, and I promise I'll work hard!
marzi (Casual Confident): My methods can be somewhat... unconventional, but the proof is in the pudding, Madame Sweets and I was able to earn a 4.0 GPA.
marzi (Casual Concerned): I'm also very creative and i have so many ideas for-
beatrix (Exasperated): Let me stop you right there.
beatrix (Exasperated): I'm not looking for my junior staff to reinvent the wheel.
beatrix (Dour Lookdown): The wheel, which as you can see, is rolling flawlessly the way it is.
beatrix (Idle Dour): No, you must first prove you are even capable of the basics.
beatrix (Idle Dour): (Her eyes bore into the core of Marzi's soul...)
beatrix (Idle Dour): (...and Marzi can tell she is being sized up in ways she doesn't comprehend.)
beatrix (Idle Dour): You have to prove you can follow the recipe of true success.
beatrix (Dour Lookdown): One bad review on SweetSnap...
beatrix (Dour Lookdown): ...One misfired enchantment...
beatrix (Dour Lookdown): ...And my entire legacy crumbles.
beatrix (Dour Lookdown): The world out there-
beatrix (Dour Lookdown): (She taps her cell phone screen.)
beatrix (Dour Lookdown): -is waiting for me to fail.
marzi (Casual Worried): (Marzi's confidence starts to falter.)
marzi (Casual Worried): R...Right.
marzi (Casual Worried): I understand...
marzi (Casual Worried): You're looking for someone more experienced...
marzi (Casual Worried): I...I'll just-
beatrix (Dour Lookdown): Hold.
beatrix (Unimpressed): (Beatrix sighs, rubbing her temples as if fighting a chronic headache.)
beatrix (Unimpressed): (She looks Marzi up and down one last time, an exhausted resignation in her eyes.)
beatrix (Dour Lookdown): You're...messy...you lack focus...
beatrix (Dour Lookdown): I'm going to need to spend considerable time with your training...
beatrix (Dour Lookdown): However the copper cauldrons require hand-polishing.
beatrix (Dour Lookdown): The marble floors need scrubbing.
beatrix (Dour Lookdown): The display cases need daily cleaning.
beatrix (Dour Lookdown): If you want to stand a chance at surviving in my prep room-
beatrix (Dour Lookdown): -We will start by infusing discipline in you like seeding a boiling syrup.
beatrix (Dour Lookdown): I will mold you like these chocolate sculptures, Ms. Glace, from the bottom molecule to the top.
marzi (Casual Amazed): Oh! Um, T...Thank you! I promise, I will work harder than anyone!
marzi (Casual Amazed): I'll prove to you that I have what it takes to be a world class confectioner!
marzi (Casual Amazed): I won't let you down!
beatrix (Dour Lookdown): We shall see about that, Ms. Glace...
beatrix (Dour Lookdown): Your shift starts at 5AM tomorrow morning.
beatrix (Dour Lookdown): If you are late, I will find another applicant.
beatrix (Dour Lookdown): That means 15 minutes early, Ms. Glace.
beatrix (Dour Lookdown): And for heaven's sake, don't you dare touch a single utensil until you have earned the right.
marzi (Casual Fear): Yes, Ma'am!
leave --All--
(Beatrix hands Marzi's portfolio over to her and she walks towards the exit, leaving the wonderous scents and mystical confections behind her.)
(Once more she pushes open the heavy doors to the street.)
